<h1>Problem 409 - 2019 BMO1, P6 of 6</h1>
<h2 class='difficulty'>Difficulty: 6</h2>
<p>A function \(f\) is called \(good\) if it assigns an integer value \(f(m, n)\) to every ordered pair of integers \((m, n)\) in such a way that for every pair of integers \((m, n)\) we have:
\[2f(m, n) = f(m-n, n-m) + m + n = f(m+1, n) + f(m, n+1) - 1.\]
Find all good functions.</p>
